cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design and optimization of a Fog Radio Access Network (F-RAN) which is a type of wireless network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the optimization of backhaul traffic balancing which involves the transmission of information over a network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the joint optimization of beamforming and clustering to minimize power consumption while meeting QoS requirements. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of caching to reduce the burden on backhaul links, which is relevant to multimedia content delivery. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of dynamic clustering in a distributed network.
